title: Independent candidate Yasir Qureshi wins PP-25 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Independent candidate, Yasir Mahmood Qureshi has won the election for Punjab Assembly constituency PP-25, Jehlum-II by securing 67,391 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Pakistan Muslim League (N) candidate, Chaudhry Nadeem Khadim who bagged 40,560 votes.
Overall votersâ€™ turn-out remained 41.80%.
